Great Expectations (GX) is an open-source data quality 
framework that allows you to:

  Define   → What your data SHOULD look like (Expectations)
  Validate → Whether your data MEETS those expectations
  Document → Auto-generate data quality reports
  Alert    → Fail pipelines when data quality drops

Key Concepts:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Expectation    │ A rule about your data             │
│                 │ e.g. "column must not be null"     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Expectation    │ Collection of expectations         │
│  Suite          │ for a dataset                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Data Source    │ Connection to your data            │
│                 │ (Spark, Delta, Pandas)             │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Checkpoint     │ Runs validation + saves results    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Data Docs      │ Auto-generated HTML reports        │
│                 │ showing pass/fail results          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
